OL,3,CViolent crimes against women on
OL,4,CBritain's trains jump by more than 50%
OL,6,FViolent attacks against women on
OL,7,FBritish railways have more than
OL,8,Fdoubled since 2021, according to new
OL,9,Fdata.
OL,11,FFigures from the British Transport
OL,12,FPolice Authority's 2024 annual report
OL,13,Fshowed the number of crimes against
OL,14,Fwomen and girls rose from 7,561 in
OL,15,F2021 to 11,357 in 2023.
OL,17,FThe number of sexual offences jumped
OL,18,F10% over the same period, while sexual
OL,19,Fharassment reports doubled, the data
OL,20,Ffirst reported by The Times also
OL,21,Frevealed.
